      "writtenOn": "2021-03-14T19:49:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I can get why DeleteQueue can be useful -- data retention policy,\nbut why CreateQueue? Who\u0027s supposed to call it \u0026 when?\n\nFYI, my two ideas:\n\n1. PM creates \u0026\u0026 updates config opts in the SQ.\nThen, this s/Create/Update. I guess it can also do delete upon project deletion.\n\n2. TryAcquire does it all in a transaction:\n * create if not exists\n * update config if necessary\n\nI slightly prefer #2, as it\u0027ll be a bit easier to evolve to more granular SQs if we have to in the future.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "8837ed02716c6ced84a2e5f2c9afebef3ae063ce",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3b306f9d_b09cff91",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/submit/queue.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 52,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-16T17:32:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My idea is exactly the #1 and agree that it should be UpdateQueue.\n\nI agree that #2 will benefit us more in the future. However, one downside of #2 is that it will require RM load the config everytime before acquiring to fetch the SubmitOptions even though it is cheap. I think we can either cache SubmitOptions inside Run entity or store some kind of version in both SubmitOptions and Run entity to perform fast comparison. WDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "54004926_134687ab",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 52,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 52,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "8837ed02716c6ced84a2e5f2c9afebef3ae063ce",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "902dcd9c_0de930d1",
        "filename": "cv/internal/run/impl/submit/queue.go",
